    • Method Detail

      • getJobsForTimePeriod

        public java.util.List<Job> getJobsForTimePeriod(int maxResults,
                                                java.time.Duration duration)
        Queries the server for the list of available Job entries with a submit date within the specified time interval. Results are returned for the time period from the current time minus the specified duration up to the current time (e.g. Duration.ofHours(24) returns jobs from the last 24 hours). The maxResults parameter specifies the maximum number of results to return. The valid range for maxResults is 0 to 10000 inclusive.
        Parameters:
        maxResults - Maximum results to return
        duration - Time interval for the job query
        Returns:
        List of jobs, empty list if none found
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if maxResults is negative
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if duration is null less than or equal to zero
        CardServicesApiException - if a server error occurs
        CardServicesException - if response deserialization fails

      • getJobsForDateRange

        public java.util.List<Job> getJobsForDateRange(int maxResults,
                                               java.time.ZonedDateTime startDate,
                                               java.time.ZonedDateTime endDate)
        Queries the server for the list of available Job entries with a submit date within the specified date range. Results are returned where the job submit date is greater than or equal to the start date and less than or equal to the end date. Care must be take when specifying the dates to avoid unexpected results due to time zone differences. The server sends dates and times in UTC and requires the client to provide accurate timezone information when submitting requests. The valid range for maxResults is 0 to 10000 inclusive.
        Parameters:
        maxResults - Maximum results to return
        startDate - Starting date for the job query
        endDate - Ending date for the job query
        Returns:
        List of jobs, empty list if none found
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if maxResults is negative
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the start date or end date is null
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the start date is later than the end date
        CardServicesApiException - if a server error occurs
        CardServicesException - if response deserialization fails

      • submitProductionRequest

        public java.lang.String submitProductionRequest(ProductionRequestTemplate requestTemplate)
        Submits the specified production request to the server for processing. On success, the method returns the job unique Id which can be used to retrieve job status information from the server.
        Parameters:
        requestTemplate - Production request template
        Returns:
        Job unique identifier
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if request template argument is null
        CardServicesException - if request validation fails
